HEADWORD: ozena
<hw>o*ze"na</hw> <pr>(⟦osl⟧*z⟦emac⟧"n⟦adot⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[NL., fr. L. <ets>ozaena</ets>, Gr. <grk>'o`zaina</grk>, fr.
<grk>'o`zein</grk> to smell.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A discharge
of fetid matter from the nostril, particularly if associated with
ulceration of the soft parts and disease of the bones of the
nose.</def></p>

<p><ent>ozocerite</ent>⟦br⟧
